theorem Topology.P1_of_P2_closure {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X}
    (h : Topology.P2 (X := X) (closure A)) :
    Topology.P1 (X := X) A := by
  -- Unfold definitions of `P2` and `P1`.
  dsimp [Topology.P2] at h
  dsimp [Topology.P1]
  intro x hxA
  -- From `A ⊆ closure A`, we have `x ∈ closure A`.
  have hx_closureA : (x : X) ∈ closure (A : Set X) := subset_closure hxA
  -- Apply `P2` for `closure A`.
  have hx_interior :
      x ∈ interior (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))) := h hx_closureA
  -- Relate the two interiors via the monotonicity lemma.
  have h_subset :
      interior (closure (interior (closure (A : Set X)))) ⊆
        closure (interior (A : Set X)) :=
    Topology.interior_closure_interior_subset_closure_interior_closure
      (X := X) (A := A)
  -- Conclude that `x ∈ closure (interior A)`.
  exact h_subset hx_interior
